metadata:
  section_id: 12
  hadith_first: 2182
  hadith_last: 2209

hadiths[28]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
2182,"I said, ""O Prophet of Allah, the saying of Allah to them is glad tidings in this worldly life."" He said, ""You asked me about something that no one before you or anyone from my Ummah has asked me about."" He said, ""It is the righteous vision that a Muslim sees or is shown.""",,,
2183,A believer’s vision is the forty-sixth part of Prophecy. (Using translation from Abū Dāʾūd 5018),,,
2184,"“I heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ say: ‘Prophecy is gone, but good dreams remain.’” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3896)",,,
2185,"“Whoever sees me in a dream has (really) seen me, for Satan cannot appear in my form.” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3901)",,,
2186,He who saw me in dream in fact saw the truth (what is true). (Using translation from Muslim 2267a),,,
2187,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said, ""A good dream is from Allah, and a bad dream is from Satan. So if anyone of you sees a dream that he dislikes, let him spit to his left three times and seek refuge in Allah from Satan, for it will not harm him.""",,,
2188,"I used to see (such horrible dreams) that I fell ill. I saw Abu Qatada who also said: I used to see dreams which made me sick until I heard Messenger of Allah ﷺ as saying: Good dreams are from Allah, so if any one of you sees which he likes he should not disclose it to one but whom he loves, but if he sees something which he does not like he should spit on his left side thrice and seek refuge with Allah from the mischief of the Satan and its mischief (i.e. of the dream), and he should not relate it to anyone, then it would not harm him. (Using translation from Muslim 2261g)",,,
2189,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said, ""Dreams are of three types: a good dream is glad tidings from Allah, a bad dream is from Shaytan, and a dream that a person narrates about himself. So, if any one of you sees a dream that he dislikes, let him not speak about it, and let him pray and seek protection from it.""",,,
2190,"“When the end of time draws near, hardly any believer will see a false dream, and the ones who see the truest dreams will be the ones who are truest in speech. And the dream of the believer is one of the forty-six parts of prophecy.’” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3917)",,,
2191,"Narrated by Ali, the Prophet ﷺ said: ""Whoever lies in his dreams will be tasked with tying two barley stalks together on the Day of Judgment.""",,,
2192,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said, ""The most truthful of dreams are those seen in the pre-dawn hours.""",,,
2193,"About the Prophet ﷺ, he used to say, ""Do not interpret dreams except by a knowledgeable person or an advisor.""",,,
2194,"He heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ say, ""Dreams are like a bird perched on a man, as long as it is not mentioned, it will occur.""",,,
2195,"I heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  saying, ""I saw my Lord in the best form."" He said, ""In what did the highest assembly differ?"" So I said, ""You know best, O Lord."" He said, ""He placed His hand between my shoulders, and I felt its coolness between my chest, and thus I knew what is in the heavens and the earth. And [Allah said], 'And thus We show Abraham the realm of the heavens and the earth that he would be among the certain [in faith].'""",,,
2196,"""Whoever sees his Lord in a dream will enter paradise.""",,,
2197,"While I was asleep I saw people being presented to me (in a dream) and they wore shirts and some of these reached up to the breasts and some even beyond them. Then there happened to pass 'Umar b. Khattab and his shirt had been trailing. They said: Allah's Messeneer, how do you interpret the dream? He said: (As strength of) faith. (Using translation from Muslim 2390)",,,
2198,"I was in the time of the Prophet ﷺ, and I had nowhere to stay except in the Prophet's Mosque. Whenever the Prophet ﷺ would wake up in the morning, people would come to him and narrate their dreams to him. So I said, ""Why don't I see anything?"" Then I saw as if people were being gathered and thrown onto their faces in a pit. I was taken and when I approached the well, a man said, ""Take him with the right group."" When I woke up, my dream bothered me, so I asked Hafsah about it. She said, ""Yes, what did you see?"" So I said, ""Ask the Prophet ﷺ about it."" So she asked him, and he said, ""Indeed, the man is Abdullah. If he were to offer the night prayer.""",,,
2199,"Helpful, and Ibn Umar used to pray at night.",,,
2200,"""I heard the Prophet ﷺ  say that while I was asleep, I was brought a cup of milk, and I drank from it until I could see the whiteness in my nails or he said, in my finger nails. Then I handed the remaining portion to Umar. They asked, 'O Messenger of Allah, what did you interpret from this?' He said, 'Knowledge.'""",,,
2201,"Some of the companions of the Prophet ﷺ  told me that the Prophet ﷺ  said, ""Milk is natural, swimming is a salvation, camels bring sadness, greenery is paradise, and women are good.""",,,
2202,"I had a dream of a cloud with shade dripping butter and honey. I saw the people scooping it up with their hands, some taking much and some taking little. I saw a rope extending from the sky to the earth. Then I saw you O Messenger of Allah ! You took hold of it and went up, then a man took hold of it after you do so, then a man took hold of it after him to do so. Then a man took hold of it and it was severed, and then connected for him, and he did so (i.e. , went up). Abu Bakr said: ""May my father and mother be ransomed for you O Messenger of Allah! Allow me to interpret it."" He said: ""Interpret it."" so he said: ""As for the cloud with its shade, it is Islam. As for what the butter and honey that dropped from it, this is the Quran and its delicateness and sweetness. It means some of them gathered much of the Quran and some of them a little. As for the rope extending from the sky to the earth, it is the truth which you are upon, you clug to it and Allah exalted you. Then another man will take hold of it after you and ascend on it, then after him, another man will take hold of it and ascend on it. Then another [man] will take hold of it but it will break, then be connected so he will ascend on it. Inform me O Messenger of Allah! Am I correct or am I mistaken?"" The Prophet ﷺ said: ""You are correct in some of it and mistaken in some of it."" He (i.e., Abu Bakr) said: ""I swear to you by my father and my mother O Messenger of Allah! Inform me in what I was mistaken?"" The Prophet ﷺ said: ""Do not swear."" (Using translation from Tirmidhī 2293)",,,
2203,"It seemed as if the sun or the moon was suspended on the Earth, with strong chains. Abu Ja'far had doubts about it, so he mentioned that to the Prophet Muhammad, peace be upon him. The Prophet replied, ""That is the death of your nephew, meaning the Messenger of Allah himself.""",,,
2204,"“In a dream I saw myself emigrating from Makkah to a land in which there were date-palm trees, and I thought that it was Yamamah or Hajar, but it was Al-Madinah, Yathrib. And I saw in this dream of mine that I was wielding a sword then it broke in the middle. That was what befell the believers on the Day of Uhud. Then I wielded it again and it was better than it had been before, and that is what Allah brought about of the Conquest and the regrouping of the believers. And I also saw cows, and by Allah it is good, for they are the group of the believers (who were martyred) on the Day of Uhud, and the goodness is that which Allah brought forth after that, and the reward of the truth which Allah brought us on the Day of Badr.” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3921)",,,
2205,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, ""I saw as if I were in a fortified shield and I saw a cow being slaughtered. I interpreted the shield to be Madinah and the cow to be a group of people. By Allah, they are better off if we confront them when they enter upon us."" They said, ""By Allah, they have never entered upon us during the pre-Islamic times. Will they then enter upon us during Islam?"" He said, ""That is your concern then."" Some of the Ansar said to each other, ""We will discuss the Prophet's ﷺ matter in his presence."" So they went to him and said, ""O Messenger of Allah, what is your opinion?"" He said, ""Now, if a prophet wears an armor for his people, he should not take it off until he fights.""",,,
2206,"From the Prophet ﷺ , it is narrated that he used to say, ""I dislike extremism and I love moderation. Moderation is firmness in religion.""",,,
2207,"I heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  saying, ""I saw in a dream a black woman with disheveled hair being expelled from the city and settled in Mahyah, and then I interpreted it as an epidemic hitting Madinah being transferred by Allah to Mahyah.""",,,
2208,"On the authority of the Prophet ﷺ, he said one day, ""Indeed, I saw in a dream that a man came to me with a bunch of dates, and I ate them. Then I found a seed in them that harmed me when I chewed it. Then he gave me another bunch of dates."" So I said, ""When I ate what you gave me, I found a seed in it that harmed me."" Abu Bakr said, ""Your eyes found sleep, O Messenger of Allah. This is the secret mission that you sent, both of which they captured, and they found a man seeking your protection. So I said to Mujalid, 'What is he seeking your protection for?' He said, 'He says, ""There is no god but Allah"".'""",,,
2209,"Narrated Aisha, the wife of the Prophet: ""There was a woman from the people of Medina who had a merchant husband. They used to have disputes, and whenever her husband was absent, she would see a dream. Every time he was away, she would see in her dream that the roof of her house had collapsed and that she had given birth to a male child who was blind in one eye. So, she would come to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  and say, 'My husband has gone out as a merchant, and he has left me behind while I am pregnant. I have seen in my dream what a sleeper sees.?' The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  would say: 'Good, it will be as you have seen it,' and she would return to her house. Indeed, her husband would return to her, and she would give birth to a male child who was blind in one eye. This happened two or three times, and every time she would see the dream, she would come to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  and tell him about it. Once, she came to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  while he was absent, and she had seen the dream. She said to me, 'What do you advise me to do? Should I ask the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  about it?' I said, 'Yes.' So, when the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  came, she told him about it. He said to her, 'What is your desired outcome?' She replied, 'By Allah, if your interpretation is true, my husband will die and I will give birth to a male child who will eventually become evil.' Then, she started weeping. The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  entered the room while she was weeping and asked her what was wrong. She told him what she had said and how she had interpreted the dream. The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said, 'O Aisha, tell her that when you see a dream, it is either about what you have seen or about what the person who sees it interprets it to be. Her husband will die, and by Allah, she will give birth to a male child who will eventually become evildoer.'",,,
